Happy New year ❤️
I start this new year with fresh optimism, and a sparkle in my eye, as I reflect on all of the love and support I have in my life. Thank you to my amazing clients, that support my artistic visions, and always find new ways to challenge me.
Thank you to my family for showing me that love is not always perfect, it can be messy, and beautiful at the same time. We grow strong like a tree, with the  best roots growing from compassion and understanding . 
To my friends, thank you for loving me, and lifting me, and  having the courage to tell me things i don’t always want to hear.
Finally thank you to life, for the times you made me uncomfortable, and it made me change for the better. 
I will try to grow bigger this year, shine brighter, and do it all with patience, compassion, and love. Thank you all, I wish you a new year filled with love, and lots of magic

This New Year’s eve, I had the pleasure of being hired to body paint two models as white tigers. I originally thought white tigers had black stripes like zebras, but they actually have thin grey stripes. 
I painted my models, and then the chef turned them into living sushi tables. What a wild party, and what a house! Outside were 4 real white tiger cubs, a mermaid swimming in the pool, and so much more. I didn’t get too much footage because I started hanging out , and I completely forgot. 😅 
.
Thank you @eatsushinaked @chefmjscharaga for having me
